5.22.25  11:27 am   when writing lyrics, what do you consider to be more important: the sound/mouthfeel, or the meaningfulness (literal or emotional)?
of course it's great when you can have both. but let's say you're writing a song and you have two drafts for a line, one where the lyrics sound good but don't really have a deeper meaning, versus one where the lyrics have deep emotional impact but sound clunky. you like both versions, but try as you might, you can't reconcile them into a hybrid version. which do you choose?

      this doesn't happen to me. you are describing 2 worlds which for me were fused together long long long long ago. additionally the melody and music is a massive factor, which for me are not separate worlds either

5.22.25  2:41 am   i feel like each project i work on, sucks. maybe i'll feel some small amounts of motivation while working on the project, but the more i work on it, the more disgusting it becomes to me. and then i take a quick look at my friend's project: it's so much better than mine. my friend tells me that my project is "so good", and i just simply don't believe him. i think he's just trying not to "hurt my feelings" by giving me the cold hard truth, as most friends would. but i have no evidence whatsoever. are my skills really terrible? is it ok to feel this way towards my projects? and is there a way out of this mess?

      the way you feel is completely normal. i don't know a solution to it. the more refined and keen your talents and senses get, the worse this problem may get
